On Sun, 8 Jan 2006, Mark Crispin wrote:
> What was a KL-UDGE?

Time's up.

The KL-UDGE was a custom-built hardware device on the MIT Macsyma 
Consortium (MIT-MC) computer, which was one of the first KL10 systems. 
Among other things, the KL-UDGE provided:
  . MIT-MC's interface to the IMP (and hence ARPAnet)
  . a date/time clock that would persist across system reboots
  . console lights

